                            <comment id="17602953" author="JIRAUSER295625" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2022 05:53:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, is there any progress on that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17603038" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2022 10:46:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Our HTML mime type has both root-XML tags for well-formed documents, and a bunch of magic for the rest. So, adding some magic as well for these documents is in theory possible&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checking for &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;svg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; with a decent priority should be fine, but I&apos;m not sure we&apos;d want to look for just &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;svg&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tallison&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tallison&quot;&gt;tallison&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17635630" author="tsuyoshizawa" created="Fri, 18 Nov 2022 03:16:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Checking for&#160;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;svg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;with a decent priority should be fine, but I&apos;m not sure we&apos;d want to look for just&#160;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;svg&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like a good idea to look at the xmlns attribute first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
